Here are both approaches:

## 1. Route Registration (AppShell.xaml.cs)

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

## 2. Navigating from ProductListPage

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

## 3. Receiving Data via IQueryAttributable

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter arrives as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B — complex object arrives as-is
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

## 4. Wire the ViewModel to the Page

```xml
<!-- ProductDetailsPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailsViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>
    <!-- Shell calls ApplyQueryAttributes on the BindingContext automatically -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- **String params** (`?productId=42`) — simple, bookmark-friendly, but limited to strings. Good when you only need an ID to fetch data.
- **`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`** — passes the live object in memory with no serialization. Use when the caller already has the object and you want to avoid a redundant lookup.
- Shell automatically calls `ApplyQueryAttributes` on the page's `BindingContext` if it implements `IQueryAttributable` — no manual wiring needed.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
